  "elapsed_s": 6.1,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "--interview with Irving Rubenstein.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "June 1, 1995.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "When the Russian-- when the Russians start pushing, the front changed.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "By Stalingrad, they start pushing towards Poland.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "Then the trouble start to begin.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "[PAUSES FOR 9 SECONDS] As the Russian army moved into Poland, the borders changed.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "[PAUSES FOR 5 SECONDS] And the Polish-- when the Russian army came closer and closer to Warsaw, [PAUSES FOR 5 SECONDS] they ordered the Polish people to make a revolt against the Nazis, against the Germans in Poland.",
      "word_count": 38
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "I were in the camp, still in Kielce.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "Yeah.",
      "word_count": 1
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Everything, what people told us, from underground newspapers, trains that went through the city.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "People used to come from Warsaw, people who listened, mostly, from British news, British news, British radio.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "Polish people had radios in the basement and used to listen from London the news at night.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Well, in giving us hope.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "We figured we lived by hour.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "There is always hope.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "It was a chance to survive.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "The closer they came, the more hope we had-- had.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "So while the Russian armies came into Poland, [PAUSES FOR 4 SECONDS] the Russian people gave an order to the Polish underground to revolt against the Germans.",
      "word_count": 27
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "[PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] And while-- as the Polish people were revolted, the Russian army stopped and waited till the Germans should kill off the intelligence.",
      "word_count": 26
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "And then they would march in.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "And that's what happened.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "The Russian army stopped for several week, Hitler took action, start transporting the Polish intelligence, the Polish intellectuals, the respectable people from the cities, the mayors, the chief of police.",
      "word_count": 30
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "They started to liquidate the Polish intelligence.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "It didn't make no difference to me, but those were the atrocities of the war, you know, as the war went on.",
      "word_count": 22
    }
  ],
